# Plan storage convention

All implementation plan markdown files for this repository MUST be stored in
`docs/plans/` (the project's design/plans folder), NOT in the default
`~/.cursor/plans/` cache. The team treats these plans as project artifacts
that get committed alongside code, reviewed in PRs, and referenced from
other docs.

## Naming

Use the existing convention already established in `docs/plans/`:

```
docs/plans/<YYYY-MM-DD>-<short-slug>.md
```

- `<YYYY-MM-DD>` — the date the plan was first drafted, e.g. `2026-04-25`.
- `<short-slug>` — kebab-case description, e.g. `mobile-campaign-approval-block`.

Examples already in the repo:

- `docs/plans/2026-04-02-central-campaign-approval-flow.md`
- `docs/plans/2026-04-06-meeting-brief-enhancement.md`
- `docs/plans/2026-03-25-voice-entry-for-chat.md`

## When using Cursor's CreatePlan tool

`CreatePlan` writes to `~/.cursor/plans/` by default. After creating a plan
that way, immediately move (or duplicate) it into `docs/plans/<date>-<slug>.md`
so the plan is part of the workspace and survives across machines/sessions.
Subsequent edits should happen on the `docs/plans/` copy.

If a plan was created in `~/.cursor/plans/` in error, relocate it to
`docs/plans/` and treat the workspace copy as the canonical version.

## Cross-references

When linking from other docs (READMEs, design notes, PRs), reference the
`docs/plans/...` path so the link is portable:

```markdown
See [campaign approval block plan](../docs/plans/2026-04-25-mobile-campaign-approval-block.md).
```
